   <head>TO THE READER.</head>
   <p>
      <seg rend="decorInit">C</seg>Ourteous Reader, whereas I was
fullie determined to haue con<g ref="char:EOLhyphen"/>cealed
my Sonnets, as thinges
priuie to my selfe, yet of courte<g ref="char:EOLhyphen"/>sie
hauing lent them to some,
they were secretlie committed to the Presse,
and almost finished, before it came to my
knowledge. Wherefore making, as they say,
<hi>Vertue of necessitie,</hi> I did deeme it most
conuenient to praepose mine Epistle, onely to
beseech you to account of them as of toyes and
amorous deuises, and ere long, I will impart
<pb facs="3"/>
vnto the world another Poeme which shall be
both more fruitfull and ponderous. In the
meane while I commit these as a pledge
vnto your indifferent cen<g ref="char:EOLhyphen"/>sures.
London,
1594.</p>
   <closer>
      <signed>W. Percy.</signed>
   </closer>
</div>
